The paper deals with the computation of Nash equilibria in congestion games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm presented in the paper is based on potential functions and their properties, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The use of approximation algorithms and analysis of approximation guarantees is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the running time of the algorithm, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.SI).
